# Start of question: interference pattern dependence on slit separation
:TYPE:MC:1:0:C
:TITLE:interference pattern dependence on slit separation
:FEEDBACK:H

:QUESTION:H
A laser shines on an adjustable double slit (the slit separation, d, can
be changed). If the slit separation is increased while the laser shines on
the double slit then the fringes in the interference pattern will
:IMAGE:
:LAYOUT:vertical
:ANSWERORDER:randomized
:INDICES:letters
:ANSWER1:100:H
move closer together.
:ANSWER2:0:H
stay the same.
:ANSWER3:0:H
move farther apart.
:ANSWER4:0:H
disappear.
:ANSWER5:0:H
The fringes close to the middle will move closer together and the ones towards the edges of the pattern will move farther apart.
:CAT:Wave Optics
# End of question: interference pattern dependence on slit separation

